Reference-contexts: External modules talk to Geomview using the Geomview Command Language (GCL), which provides support for controlling almost all aspects of Geomview's behavior. Geomview can display manifolds through discrete group support and an external module, Maniview <ref> [Gun93] </ref>. Maniview provides a user interface for loading and displaying 3-manifolds. While a manifold is infinite in extent, graphics hardware can only display a finite number of polygons. <p> The complete interface should be capable of all the things currently possible in Maniview. Developing such a complex interface with the low resolution of today's helmet displays calls for creative solutions, such as virtual data column used by the Sparcchair [Rei93]. Charlie Gunn <ref> [Gun93] </ref> suggests that using sound in a virtual environment may help in exploring and understanding manifolds. Determining echo patterns in a manifold is a challenging and interesting problem. Not all work in non-euclidean spaces deals directly with mathematics.
